.TH "epf_ntb_link_up" 9 "epf_ntb_link_up" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
epf_ntb_link_up \- Raise link_up interrupt to both the hosts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" epf_ntb_link_up
.BI "(struct epf_ntb *ntb "  ","
.BI "bool link_up "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ntb" 12
NTB device that facilitates communication between HOST1 and HOST2
.IP "link_up" 12
true or false indicating Link is UP or Down
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Once NTB function in HOST1 and the NTB function in HOST2 invoke
\fBntb_link_enable\fP, this NTB function driver will trigger a link event to
the NTB client in both the hosts.
